Blood oxygen saturation (SpO2) is a measure of the blood\'s ability to carry oxygen. It is the percentage of the volume of oxygenated hemoglobin combined with oxygen in the blood to the total volume of hemoglobin that can be combined, that is, the concentration of blood oxygen in the blood, which is the respiratory cycle Important physiological parameters. Ideally, blood oxygen saturation should be 95%-100%, but it will vary depending on the individual\'s physical condition, altitude, and certain diseases. Please note that this feature is not designed for medical use. If you have any questions or health issues, please consult a healthcare professional.

Blood pressure (BP) refers to the lateral pressure of blood in the arterial tube against the vessel wall. The highest blood pressure during systole is called systolic blood pressure (high pressure), and the lowest blood pressure during diastole is called diastolic blood pressure (low pressure). Normal systolic blood pressure of adults generally does not exceed 140 mmHg (18.7 kPa), and diastolic blood pressure is below 90 mmHg (12 kPa). However, it will be different due to personal physical condition and certain diseases. Please note that this feature is not designed for medical use. If you have any questions or health issues, please consult a healthcare professional.
Normal blood pressure:\n90mmHg< systolic blood pressure<140mmHg \n60mmHg< diastolic blood pressure<90mmHg
Note: This measurement result is for reference only and cannot replace medical diagnosis

There are differences in body temperature between morning and evening, various parts of the human body, and between men and women. The normal body temperature of the human body has a relatively stable range, but it is not constant. The normal oral temperature (also called oral temperature) is %1$s, and the axillary temperature is %2$s lower than the oral temperature. During the day, the body temperature is lowest at 2 to 5 in the morning and highest at 5 to 7 in the afternoon, but the temperature difference within a day should be less than %3$s. In addition, women\'s body temperature is generally about %4$s higher than that of men. Women\'s body temperature also changes slightly during menstruation.

Normal body temperature:\nThe normal body temperature of the human body averages between %1$s (armpit). If it exceeds %2$s, it means fever, %3$s is low fever, and %4$s is high fever. Above %5$s, life is in danger at any time.

Heart rate is the frequency of the heart beating,expressed by the number of heart beats per minute, and it is usually 50~100 beats/min for adults in the state of lung activity.The heart provides blood circulation, oxygen and nutrients to the body, and heart rate can be regarded as an important indicator of cardiovascular health. Heart rate varies from person to person due to age, gender or other physiological factors. In general, the older you are, the faster your heart rate is, and women\'s heart rates are faster than boys of the same age. Heart rate during sleep is generally lower than when awake, and heart rate during exercise varies with exercise intensity. \nPlease note that this feature is not designed for medical use, please consult a healthcare professional if you have any questions or health concerns.

The device analyzes changes in physical activity to estimate your sleep time and sleep status. Sleep data can help you understand, manage your sleep habits and improve sleep quality. Good sleep can not only help the human body recover physical strength, enhance resistance, promote human metabolism, but also be good for mental health. \nPlease note that this feature is not designed for medical use, please consult a healthcare professional if you have any questions or health concerns.

Heart rate zone=(220-age)*Maximum heart rate percentage range
50%~60%: Warm up body and mind rate range, used to cultivate physical fitness or warm up before exercise. Type of exercise, such as brisk walking.
60%~70%: Fat burning heart rate range, used to improve basic physical fitness, help increase fat release rate, and regulate cardiovascular. Type of exercise, such as jogging.

70%~80%: aerobic endurance heart rate range, used for endurance training, it is beneficial to improve aerobic fitness, increase lung capacity, and control breathing rhythm. Type of exercise, such as easy running.

80%~90%: Anaerobic endurance heart rate range, used for speed improvement training, which is beneficial to improve physical fitness. It is necessary to properly control the exercise time in this range. Type of exercise, such as rhythm running or interval running training.

90%~100%: Limit heart rate range, used for explosive training. At this time, lactic acid accumulates rapidly and is easy to be injured. The exercise time in this range needs to be strictly controlled. Type of exercise, such as extreme running.

Heart rate variability (HRV) refers to the time used to measure the interval between heartbeats. Heart rate variability contains information on the regulation of the cardiovascular system by glenohumeral factors, and then it can be used to determine the status and prevention of cardiovascular and other diseases. This will also be possible It is a valuable indicator for the prediction of sudden cardiac death and arrhythmia. When you\'re under some kind of stress, your heart rate usually increases and your heart rate variability decreases, with lower heart rate variability corresponding to higher stress.

When the scheduled HRV monitoring device is turned on, the device will automatically monitor HRV at regular intervals, which can provide you with more accurate data while taking into account power consumption.
